main event: A radar operator sighted five unidentified objects on September 27, 1961.
interesting points: Objects were moving at a high rate of speed and disappeared into sea clutter., Two objects later appeared and moved across the radar scope., Speed of one object was measured at 1900 knots over a distance of 22 nautical miles., An additional stationary object appeared on radar after the two objects were sighted., Weather conditions were clear with no temperature inversion.
